c: 46
v: 11
t: "And those who deny Allah speak of those who sincerely believed in Him, and say: \"If it -the Quran- were good and has a quality in a sufficient degree, we would have been the first to take it as a matter of choice;\" and so, since they respond to the Quran with careless disinterested spirit and disfavour, they will label it: \"fables of old"